Basics of Computer Networks  

Computer :Network - A network is group of connected nodes that can communicate the data and share the resources.

The Internet is the example of computer network which connects the multiple devices accross the world .

The network is made up of three major components are Node,Networking device and transmission medium .

Node - Any devices that can transmits or receive the data is known as Node.
Example : - Laptop,mobile phones ,computer etc.
Types of node :-
Client - A node that request the service in the network is known as client .
Ex : - laptop ,mobile 
Server - A node that provide service to the client is known as server .
Ex : - Web server ,mobile server ,database server etc.

Nodes are connected through transmission medium in the network .

Trasmission meduim can either wired like optical fiber ,coaxial cable or wireless like wifi or bluetooth 

Networking devices are used to provide the different functionality in the network and used to running the different protocols .
Router ,Switch and firewall are different example of different networking devices.

